<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKL-MERCURY-MYSTIC-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BENCHING SPARKS NEWCOMER  
 DAVIS-WRIGHTSIL KEYS 2ND-HALF RALLY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By JEFF METCALFE  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ It wasn't a $500 fine by the WNBA or even being
taken out of the Mercury's starting lineup Tuesday that woke up
Clarissa Davis-Wrightsil.
</P>
<P>
   She made that decision herself after managing no points or
rebounds Monday, her second double zilch in three games.
Davis-Wrightsil even stood up before her teammates to say as much
after an 80-76 loss to Orlando.
</P>
<P>
   ``I couldn't contribute yesterday,'' she said. ``I was in foul
trouble, and I couldn't do a dang-gum thing. That bothered me, and
I felt I had a responsibility to say that. I wanted them to know
that it matters that I'm not out there being able to contribute.
</P>
<P>
   ``All I can do is go in and do what I did today.''
</P>
<P>
   What she did was shoot 7 for 11, including three three-pointers,
in a 19-point second half to lift the Mercury (2-3) from a 19-point
first-half deficit to a 79-76 win over the Washington Mystics
(1-5).
</P>
<P>
   Davis-Wrightsil finished with a team-high 23 points in 24
minutes, the kind of scoring Phoenix expected in expending a
second-round draft pick on the 6-foot-1 forward and essentially
handing her a starting job from that day forward.
</P>
<P>
   But the 32-year-old sat out much of training camp to prevent a
tender right foot from developing a serious injury. Then after
three quick buckets in the Mercury's opening game, she went south.
</P>
<P>
   The fine, for an elbow to the throat of Cleveland's Eva Nemcova
on Saturday, and benching in favor of Lisa Harrison served only to
reignite Davis-Wrightsil, who scored an American Basketball League
playoff-record 36 points in Game 5 of the 1998 Finals.
</P>
<P>
   ``Walking in the locker room, she said, `Coach, you didn't have
to bench me to get my attention,' '' Mercury Coach Cheryl Miller
said. ``I said I'll bench you for the rest of the season if I can
get that type of a performance.
</P>
<P>
   ``If it works out, that will have been the master plan all along
when we drafted Clarissa and Lisa (Harrison). To have that type of
1-2 punch in the three spot. If we can get that consistently, I
really like our chances.''
</P>
<P>
   With Jennifer Gillom struggling and starting center Marlies
Askamp slowed by a nasty right knee bruise, Miller went down the
stretch mostly with a lineup of four perimeter players _ Michele
Timms, Kristi Harrower, Davis-Wrightsil and Harrison _ and 6-foot-8
Maria Stepanova.
</P>
<P>
   Davis-Wrightsil scored 13 points during an 18-2 run that brought
the Mercury from a 59-43 hole to even at 61 with 8:34 remaining.
From there it was a tight battle.
</P>
<P>
   ``You have players out there who have been playing a long
time,'' said Mystics rookie Chamique Holdsclaw, this year's No. 1
overall draft pick. ``They can make the crucial plays.''
</P>
<P>
   Like a 23-foot three-pointer by Timms with 54 seconds left to
erase Washington's last lead. Then, after Holdsclaw's short jumper
fell short, the 5-4 Harrower rebounded and Timms made the second of
two free throws for a 77-74 margin.
</P>
<P>
   Holdsclaw, who was 5 for 12 for 14 points, rimmed a layup that
Davis-Wrightsil accidentally tipped in for Washington. But Timms
hit two free throws at 4.7 seconds to ice the Mercury's first road
win and fourth straight victory over the second-year Mystics.
</P>
<P>
   Phoenix continues its seven-game swing at Charlotte (1-3) on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Washington led 36-17 in the first half before an 11-1 Phoenix
run, including five points by Edna Campbell, cut the deficit to
single digits.
</P>
<P>
   Campbell's defense early in the second half was critical, Timms
said, in bridging the gap. Then Davis-Wrightsil caught fire.
</P>
<P>
   ``When coach had words with us after the (Monday) game and asked
for any comments, Chloe (Davis-Wrightsil) was the only person who
said anything,'' Timms said. ``She just said I'd really like to
apologize for what I didn't do, my mind wasn't there. That must
have been a real kick in the butt for her not to start tonight.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
