<P>
   LABUTE-PROFILE (Undated) _ For many moviegoers there is almost
nothing like sitting through a Neil LaBute film. Nothing more
depressing on screen. Nothing more likely to induce despair, or
more frightening, perhaps, for what it shows us about ourselves.
Sexual cruelty. Domination. Hatred. LaBute shoves them in your
face. And now with ``bash, latterday plays,'' at the Douglas
Fairbanks Theater through July 24, LaBute has done it again, for
the stage this time. By Dinitia Smith.
