<P>
   NUDE-CHEFS (Undated) _ The ads are titled, ``famous chefs naked
with their blender.'' The first one appeared in the June issue of
Food Arts, a glossy trade magazine. In moody black and white,
Jean-Louis Palladin wears nothing but some jewelry, his glasses and
a strategically placed Vita-Prep blender. Coming models in the
naked series promise to draw even closer scrutiny: Eric Ripert, of
Le Bernardin and Aquavit's Marcus Samuelsson, two of the food
world's four-star heartthrobs. Success for the modern chef can
demand much more than just high-level cooking skills. Charm and
glamor are prerequisites. And now, so is good looks: The chef as
hunk. It's a development that some clearly revel in, others
tolerate and still others find silly and trivializing. By Rick
