<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Meet that billionaire down the block
 &HT;    By Loretta Grantham
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ If you're the type who has to keep up
with the neighbors, you'll need to win the lottery _ every week for
the rest of your life.
</P>
<P>
   Forbes' 13th annual World's Billionaires List, in the magazine's
July 5 issue, includes 13 loaded guys who own homes in the Palm
Beach area. (Dropped from the list, by the way, was Donald Trump,
worth $1.5 billion in 1998 but no more.)
</P>
<P>
   Here they are, as ranked among America's richest by Forbes, with
a tidbit about each:
</P>
<P>
   24. John Kluge, Palm Beach; Metromedia Co., $10.5 billion.
Ex-wife Patricia split with $1 billion in 1991.
</P>
<P>
   90. S.I. Newhouse, Palm Beach; publishing, $4.5 billion. Irked
because NASDAQ wants to erect a giant electronic sign on Newhouse's
Conde Nast building in New York City, which would block his window.
(It's in arbitration.)
</P>
<P>
   94. Leonard A. Lauder, Palm Beach; Estee Lauder cosmetics, $4.4
billion. An avid hiker who overpacks and becomes ``a walking
closet,'' jokes wife, Evelyn.
</P>
<P>
   95. Ronald S. Lauder, Palm Beach; Estee Lauder cosmetics, $4.4
billion. Was ambassador to Austria in the mid-1980s.
</P>
<P>
   108. Ron Perelman, Palm Beach; Revlon, Sunbeam, $4.2 billion.
Spotted around town last season with actress Ellen Barkin.
</P>
<P>
   122. Charles Bronfman, Palm Beach; Seagram Co., $3.7 billion.
Created Israel Experience, a teen travel and study program.
</P>
<P>
   163. David Koch, Palm Beach; Koch Industries (an energy
conglomerate), $3 billion. Twin brother Bill _ who runs Oxbow Group
(also an energy firm) _ lives in Palm Beach, too.
</P>
<P>
   208. Jack C. Taylor, Palm Beach; Enterprise Rent-A-Car, $2.4
billion. Last year, paid $84,184.76 in property tax!
</P>
<P>
   298. James H. Clark, Palm Beach; Internet investments, $1.6
billion. Wife, Nancy, competes in Wellington's Winter Equestrian
Festival.
</P>
<P>
   305. H. Wayne Huizenga, St. Lucie County; autos, trash hauling,
$1.6 billion. Wife (and Panthers fan), Marti, paid $3,500 for a
hockey stick from Philadelphia bad boy Eric Lindros at a charity
auction. She had it smashed by another player.
</P>
<P>
   327. Richard M. DeVos, Manalapan; Amway, $1.5 billion. Received
heart from 40-year-old woman during transplant in 1997.
</P>
<P>
   382. George L. Lindemann, Palm Beach; cable TV, cell phones,
$1.3 billion. Sold Wellington home in January 1998 for $3.5
million, bought it back in August for $2.9 million, then sold it
again for $3.5 million.
</P>
<P>
   400. Richard J. Egan, Boca Raton; EMC Corp. (data storage), $1.2
billion. Put commercial division of Intel, chipmaker
extraordinaire, on the map.
</P>
<P>
   418. A. Alfred Taubman, Palm Beach; real estate, $1.2 billion.
Awarded $500,000 in 1987 against architect Richard Meier because
the home Meier designed for him leaked in nine rooms.
</P>
<P>
   425. Robert David Ziff, Palm Beach; Ziff Brothers investments,
$1.2 billion. Dad William Ziff Jr. founded PC Magazine.
</P>
<P>
   451. Sidney Kimmel, Palm Beach; apparel, $1 billion. Mansion
designed by architect Thierry Despont of New York, who oversaw 1986
restoration of the Statue of Liberty.
</P>
<P>
   Loretta Grantham writes for the Palm Beach Post, West Palm
Beach, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
