Filet with Mongo-Orange Vinegar Sauce, Red Chile Grilled Cervena
Skewers with Parmesan Cabbage Slaw.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CYBERSPICE -- It's time to sing the praises of the lowly
beet. (Parham, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) With recipe for Beets
and Carrots with West Indian Spices.
</P>
<P>
   BUDGET-PARTIES _ AUSTIN _ Another installment in the Austin
Entertains series. This one reflects entertaining on a tight budget
and features Angelica and Omar , who are typical of the 12,000 grad
students at UT. They have no money for anything, let alone parties.
But that does not stop them from having their friends over for
chicken mole, arepas or other ethnic dishes from their native
countries of Mexico and Venezuela. They are not the only ones who
have learned to party frugally. Jay Nazz, a drummer with the
Reckless Kelly band, calls on his Italian heritage and stuffs pasta
shells to entertain his friends and fellow band members. Recipes.
Sidebars: How 3 entertaining pros would spend $25 to jumpstart a
good party (12 inches). Plus other frugal tips. (A pancake
breakfast is a good, cheap way of entertaining.) (Crider, Austin
American-Statesman). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   SPEECH _ Bill Moyers examines free speech and the price we pay
for it in a new PBS documentary scheduled to air in Austin on
Friday, June 25. A review of the show and comments from Moyers.
(Holloway, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   DIVA-OVERKILL _ Everywhere you turn, there's another new diva on
the scene _ or an established singer who's suddenly been anointed
with the title. Looking for a country diva? Shania Twain's got your
number. How about a couple of divas-in-training? Consider Brandy
and Monica, who teamed up recently on The Boy Is Mine, a catfight
of a single that played into the pair's rumored rivalry. And then
there's Jewel, the sweet-singing folk diva who's been on the cover
of Time. Wait a sec: A ``folk diva''? Isn't that a contradiction in
terms? An oxymoron of the most moronic sort? Let's face it: We're
sick of divas. (Passy, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-PLAN _ Video of the week: ``A Simple Plan.'' (Murray,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 6.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-MINIS _ Mini views of new videos: ``Patch Adams,'' ``Storm
of the Century,'' ``Jawbreaker'' and ``Hurlyburly.'' (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-SPOTLIGHT _ Focus on Billy Bob Thornton of ``A Simple
Plan.'' (Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 6.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-NEXT _ Coming soon to video: ``Rushmore,'' ``The Thin Red
Line,'' ``The Hi-Lo Country,'' ``Varsity Blues,'' ``The Mighty,''
``Still Crazy'' and ``Outside Ozona.'' (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-COLUMN _ A grim masterpiece of the '70s, Martin
Scorsese'sCQ brooding, bloody ``Taxi Driver'' seems more vital than
ever in the wake of recent high school shootings, not to such
madmen as Ted KaczynskiCQ and the Centennial Olympic Park bomber. A
new collector's edition DVD offers a crisp audio-visual version of
the film, plus fine extras. These include an interactive version of
Paul Schrader'sCQ shooting script, selected storyboards, and an
hour-long documentary on the making of the 1976 movie. (Suggested
retail price: $26.99.CQ) (Murray, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
20.
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-POP _ Review of new album by Diana Krall. (Dollar, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 7.
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-ELLIOTT _ Review of new Missy Elliott album. (Murray,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-MINIS _ Reviews of Wild, Wild West soundtrack; pavement;
test (jazz group). (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
