houses all over. I knew Burt Reynolds before he was on Gunsmoke.
Ricardo Montalban. Governor Claude Kirk was my friend, used to eat
breakfast with him.'' But those old friends stopped calling and the
magic jobs went begging after Peter Gross was convicted of selling
knock-off watches and suitcases out of his house. That was 1995.
And again in 1997. He's 82 and on probation for five years. The
judge wanted to send him to jail. (Reid, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FORBES-RICHLIST _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ If you're the type who
has to keep up with the neighbors, you'll need to win the lottery _
every week for the rest of your life. Forbes' 13th annual World's
Billionaires List, in the magazine's July 5 issue, includes 13
loaded guys who own homes in the Palm Beach area. (Dropped from the
list, by the way, was Donald Trump, worth $1.5 billion in 1998 but
no more.) Here they are, as ranked among America's richest by
Forbes, with a tidbit about each. (Grantham, Palm Beach Post)
MOVED.
</P>
