gulls that have turned lunchtime into the plot of an Alfred
Hitchcock horror film. Put the humans in a cage. By PETER HARTLAUB.
</P>
<P>
   SEA-OTTERS (San Francisco) _ In a disturbing trend, the
population of California sea otters continues to fall, raising
fears that the state's popular marine mammal will one day disappear
from the rocky coastline. The spring survey conducted by teams of
scientists found 2,090 sea otters, indicating an overall decline of
1.14 percent from a survey a year ago. By JANE KAY.
