home and perform fellatio on their fathers.
 &HT;    That famous North Carolina story about the 6-year-old who was
suspended from school three years ago for kissing a classmate on
the cheek? Sure. She knows that one too.
 &HT;    Gillen rolls her eyes. ``For a while I got asked that question
just about every place I went,'' she says. ``'And what do you think
about that? How stupid can they be?' And frankly, I agreed with
them. It was stupid.''
 &HT;    For the record: The school subsequently recanted the suspension,
and the Lexington, N.C., school district revised its sex-harassment
policy to take into account the age and maturity of the accused
harasser.
 &HT;    But there's a reason people latched on with such enthusiasm to
the image of school officials banishing a 6-year-old for bussing
