<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-23 13:57 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6564 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u k &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-JACKSON-COLUMN-BOS &LR;      06-23 0865
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-JACKSON-COLUMN-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IN THE BEGINNING WAS THE WORD _ OF THE NRA 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By DERRICK Z. JACKSON  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The House last week prescribed two tablets of extra-strength
Exodus to surly adolescents for fast, safe, and very temporary
political relief from schoolyard massacres. Alabama's Robert
Aderholt, sponsor of the bill that would let states post the Ten
Commandments in public schools, said, ``it is important step to
promote morality, and an end of children killing children.''
</P>
<P>
   We all know God works in mysterious ways, but how Aderholt knows
this is truly a revelation, since the Ten Commandments he wants in
the schools are not the same ones tacked to his own door on Capitol
Hill. It is odd for Aderholt to cure trigger tremors and trenchcoat
seizures with Exodus when his own commandments come from the Book
of Exotoxin, where political poison is released into the mainstream
by the gun lobby.
</P>
<P>
   These are the commandments of Aderholt and the House:
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Then the National Rifle Association spoke all these words,
saying,
</P>
<P>
   ``I am the NRA your God, who brought you into your congressional
seat and into my House of slavery.
</P>
<P>
   ``You shall have no other gods before Me.
</P>
<P>
   ``You shall not envision an America with gun control for
yourself nor the likeness of anything for your constituents in your
district.
</P>
<P>
   ``You shall not worship such a vision or serve constituents who
want gun control; for I, the NRA your God, am a jealous God. I have
punished three and four generations of politicians since 1871; I
punished the Democrats in 1994; I will continue to punish those who
hate Me,
</P>
<P>
   ``But I will continue to show loving kindness to thousands and
give thousands of dollars of campaign contributions to those who
love Me and keep My commandments.
</P>
<P>
   ``You shall not take the name of the NRA, your God in vain, for
the LORD will not leave unpunished the man who takes His name in
vain by wanting three-day waiting periods for gun sales.
</P>
<P>
   ``Remember Election Day and keep it holy.
</P>
<P>
   ``Six days you shall tell constituents that the children are our
future and hug and kiss babies for photo-ops,
</P>
<P>
   ``But Election Day is a sabbath of the NRA your God; you shall
weaken existing gun laws and ignore unliscened gun dealers and
shoddy gun shows. You shall not do any work on behalf of gun
control, even if sons are using legally-purchased guns to spray
down other sons, daughters, teachers and parents.
</P>
<P>
   ``For in six days the NRA frantically and fanatically made the
heavens and the earth, the sea and all that is in them safe for
Smith and Wesson, Glock, Ruger and Lorcin. The NRA rested on
Election Day, knowing politicians will keep it holy.
</P>
<P>
   ``Honor Charlton Heston, that your days in office may be
prolonged in the land which the NRA your God gives you.
</P>
<P>
   ``You shall not murder, but you also shall not care if more
children murder children in the United States than the rest of the
developed world.
</P>
<P>
   ``You shall not let the fact that the Revolution was over two
centuries ago adulterate the Second Amendment.
</P>
<P>
   ``You shall not let the government steal our guns.
</P>
<P>
   ``You shall not bear false witness against your constituents
except for pseudoscientific claims that guns make us safer and
studies in medical journals which show that gun ownership actually
doubles and triples the chance of being shot.
</P>
<P>
   ``You shall not let thoughtful critics covet the high ground
when Heston and Jesse Ventura belch that pistol-packing teachers
would have stopped the bloodshed at Littleton. You shall not be
swayed by wailing mothers on the six-o'clock news. You shall not
covet gun laws in Japan, England, Germany or New Zealand.''
</P>
<P>
   When Americans saw how it thundered and the lightning flashed,
how they heard the trumpet sound and saw the mountain smoking and
the hot lava of NRA PAC money flowing down, they trembled and stood
at a distance. Most Americans want new gun restrictions, according
to polls. But they said to the House,
</P>
<P>
   ``Speak to us yourself, and we will listen. But if the NRA
speaks to us, we shall die.''
</P>
<P>
   The House answered, ``Do not be afraid. The NRA has only come to
test you, so that the fear of it may remain with you and keep you
from gun control.
</P>
<P>
   So the people stood at a distance, while the House approached
the dark cloud where the NRA was.
</P>
<P>
   The NRA said to the House, ``Ye have seen that I have bribed
you, indentured you and enslaved you.
</P>
<P>
   ``Ye shall not make laws of gun control; neither shall ye make
any gun restrictions whatsoever.
</P>
<P>
   ``An altar of guns thou shalt make unto me, and shalt sacrifice
thereon thy bullet-riddled children. There are no peace offerings,
only thy groaning emergency rooms and moaning funeral homes; in all
places where I record my name I will come unto thee and I will
bless thee.
</P>
<P>
   ``And if thou wilt make me an altar of guns, thou shalt not
build it with BB guns; for if thou bring anything less than the
most lethal, easy-to-load, armor piercing, expanding-bullet,
10-to-15-shot semiautomatic handguns, thou hast polluted it.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
(Derrick Z. Jackson is a Globe columnist.)
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
