A6587 &Cx1f; tad-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-VIDEO-PLAN24-COX     06-23 0169
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-PLAN24-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Brothers' scheme not so simple
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   A Simple Plan'' (R)
</P>
<P>
   Fans of chain saw-happy director Sam Raimi (the ``Evil Dead''
movies) won't recognize his restrained, mournful work here. That's
not a bad thing.
</P>
<P>
   Bill Paxton plays a family man in small-town, snowy Minnesota
who, with his slow-witted brother (Oscar nominee Billy Bob
Thornton) stumbles upon a crashed plane that has a corpse inside .
. . and also a bagful of $4 million in cash.
</P>
<P>
   So what's the guys' plan? Simple. Well, at first anyway. The
brothers and Thornton's best pal (Brent Briscoe) agree to split the
cash. But greed takes hold, and soon the snow is splashed with
blood.
</P>
<P>
   The movie's cold setting clashes with the eruption of hot
passions. Raimi's tone likewise strikes a balance, managing to be
tragic and darkly funny at the same time.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: B
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
