</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on. . . .
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Billy Bob Thornton (`A Simple Plan')
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``One False Move'' (1991; Rated R) _ Playing a killer heading
toward Arkansas for a showdown with lawman Bill Paxton; Thornton
co-wrote the screenplay.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Sling Blade'' (1996; Rated R) _ Shambling around as a
gentle, lethal lug and winning an Oscar for his screenplay.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Primary Colors'' (1998; Rated R) _ Spin-doctoring, James
Carville-style, in this thinly veiled comedy about the first
Clinton presidential campaign, with John Travolta and Emma
Thompson.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Armageddon'' (1998; Rated PG-13) _ Barking orders as a NASA
bigwig in this FX-driven disaster flick.
</P>
<P>
   _ Steve Murray writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
