</P>
<P>
   BBN-METS-MARLINS (New York) _ Florida at Mets, 7:40 p.m. ET. By
Joe Drape.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-BUICK-OPEN (Harrison, N.Y.) _ Buick Open: The tournament has
a surprisingly strong field considering it is just one week after
the U.S. Open. By Clifton Brown.
</P>
<P>
   With graphic showing Ryder Cup point totals.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-WIMBLEDON (Wimbledon, Eng.) _ Jim Courier upsets No. 12
Carlos Moya in a battle of former French Open champions. Courier
advanced beyond the second round at Wimbledon for the first time
since 1993. And Pete Sampras advances as well. By Robin Finn.
</P>
<P>
   TEN-HINGIS (Wimbledon, Eng.) _ Players talk about Martina
Hingis' early Wimbledon flameout, plus some information on her
mother/coach and a heel injury she says hindered her. By Robin
Finn.
</P>
<P>
   SOC-CUP-SOBRERA (Chicago) _ Advance on U.S. game against
Nigeria, focused on Kate Sobrera, a defender from Notre Dame who
could play a key role Thursday against the attacking Nigerians. By
Jere Longman.
</P>
