<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEDICARE-DRUGS (Washington) _ Lawmakers on the Senate Finance
Committee struggle to find a way to pay for proposed Medicare
coverage of prescription drugs. Unlike private insurance plans, the
government health insurance program for the elderly does not cover
the drugs. By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN.
</P>
<P>
   CISNEROS-HEARING (Washington) _ Lawyers for former Housing
Secretary Henry Cisneros continue to hammer at the credibility of
the government's key witness in its conspiracy case, and to attack
the authenticity of recordings of conversations between Cisneros
and his former mistress, Linda Jones. By GARY MARTIN.
</P>
<P>
   COURT-STATES-RIGHTS (Washington) _ The Supreme Court
substantially redraws the border between state sovereignty and
federal authority, limiting the ability of people to sue states
using federal law. In a 5-4 decision, the justices dismiss a
lawsuit by a group of state employees in Maine who sought to
enforce a federal labor law and collect overtime pay. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   FLAG-AMENDMENT (Washington) _ The House considers a proposed
constitutional amendment that would seek to protect the flag from
burning or other forms of desecration. By GREG McDONALD.
</P>
<P>
   U.S.-MEXICO (Washington) _ A New Jersey man whose wife was
brutally murdered in Sarasota, Fla., urges Congress to pressure the
Mexican government to extradite one of the suspects accused in the
crime. By JUDY HOLLAND.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   LOTTERY-TEXAS (Austin, Texas) _ Armed with a new state law,
Texas Lottery officials announce they have begun increasing the
prize payout for scratch-off games in an effort to win back
players. Texas also is negotiating with several other states on
possible participation in a multistate mega-jackpot lottery that
would be a first for Texas. By CLAY ROBISON.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-NBA (New York) _ The New York Knicks try to even the NBA
Finals at two games apiece tonight in Game 4 with the San Antonio
Spurs at Madison Square Garden. By JONATHAN FEIGEN.
</P>
<P>
   With: BKN-BLINEBURY-COLUMN
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (St. Louis) _ The Houston Astros, fresh from a
marathon game Tuesday in which they lost 4-3 in 14 innings, face
the St. Louis Cardinals again today. By JOSEPH DUARTE.
</P>
<P>
   With: BBN-ROBERTSON-COLUMN
