<HEADLINE>
KANSAS CITY STAR HAS HEMINGWAY WEB SITE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By THE KANSAS CITY STAR  
 c. 1997 The Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star maintains a Hemingway web site:
www.kcstar.com//aboutStar//hemingway//ernie.htm. It has background
on his period in Kansas City; a guide to Kansas City in his work;
the text of stories attributed to Hemingway that appeared in the
newspaper in 1917-18; and information on the annual Ernest
Hemingway Writing Scholarships, a national competition for high
school journalists.
</P>
</TEXT>
