   TRACK AND FIELD
</P>
<P>
   RUN-SPRINTERS _ EUGENE, Ore. _ Gail Devers, sprint champion of
the past two Olympics, likely will pass the torch in Sydney to new
sensation Marion Jones. Devers recently moved to Atlanta, where she
now trains to defend her Olympic title, but it will be tough
staving off Jones. They are among the stars of the U.S. Track and
Field Championships beginning Thursday. (Fish, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   OLY-HIGHJUMP-AUSTIN _ SAN MARCOS, Texas _ When he broke the
American outdoor record in the high jump, Charles Austin readily
acknowledges, ``I didn't know what I was doing. I was just goofing
around.'' The surprise, though, isn't necessarily that Austin did
what no American has ever done by clearing a bar 7 feet, 10.5
inches off the ground at an outdoor meet. Perhaps the surprise is
that he hasn't done it since that magical meet in Zurich,
Switzerland, on Aug. 7, 1991. That's especially true since the
former Southwest Texas State Bobcat, now 31, definitely knows what
he is doing and assuredly isn't goofing off. (Riggs, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   SOCCER
</P>
<P>
