Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   SOC-NATNOTES _ National soccer notebook. (Parker, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   HOCKEY
</P>
<P>
   HKN-WADDELL _ Don Waddell was never known as a physical player
in his career, which spanned one NHL game with the L.A. Kings and
several years in the minor leagues and Europe. But you'd be
hardpressed to find an NHL executive who has emerged from more
difficult times, growing up in racially torn Detroit, where he was
once was locked in a high school safe with other white kids during
a riot, been held up at gunpoint while working at a convenience
store, was nearly blinded in one eye when another player hit him
with a stick requiring surgery and growing up poor in a two-bedroom
house with five kids and a single mother. His father left home for
another woman when Waddell was young, then got into a car crash
that crippled him for life. So by comparison, forming the core of
the Atlanta Thrashers over a span of two drafts in 48 hours won't
seem so difficult for Waddell. (Schultz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 50.
</P>
