<P>
   TRAVOLTA-RESURGENCE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   DALLAS _ He's a bold and impressive actor, John Travolta _ maybe
better at playing arrogance than any other actor of his generation.
Which is why his sunny, agreeable disposition is a little
disconcerting. There have been reports of the Vulcan Mind Meld that
he employs with interviewers, turning the tables on them. But, in
Dallas to promote the new military murder mystery, ``The General's
Daughter,'' he's easygoing and open. By ELVIS MITCHELL. Story has
moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   L I F E S T Y L E &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MEN-HEALTH &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The ``stronger'' sex is beginning to toughen up,
finally. But deep down, most men don't believe that they are
Superman, and, thankfully, more and more men are showing that they
do care about staying healthy. Cheeseburgers or not, signs of a sea
change in the way men view their bodies and their health are clear.
The forces of change? Everything from Bob Dole to Propecia, and
from AIDS to HMOs. By CAROLYN POIROT. Story has moved in ``l''
lifestyle category. (Accompanied by MEN-HEALTH-TESTOSTERONE.) &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
