<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN_FT:UNDATED _ You know what's amazing about
politicians?
</P>
<P>
   Well, OK, a lot of things are amazing about politicians: their
breathtaking proclivity for deceit, their mind-boggling penchant
for manipulation, their shocking propensity for greed and
self-indulgence, their limitless capacity for trampling the
interests of the people they are elected to serve ... But the
amazing trait of which I speak is the politicians' infuriating
habit of reacting to problems by proposing solutions that have
nothing to do with the problems they propose to solve. 920 Bill
Thompson. &QL; 
