   SCOTUS-ASBESTOS (Washington) _ The Supreme Court sets aside a
$1.5 billion landmark settlement that was to have resolved the
claims of as many as 186,000 victims of asbestos poisoning against
Fibreboard Corp., one of the leading makers of products using the
fire-retardant substance. By Stephen Labaton. (Scheduled to move by
9 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.) 1,100 words.
</P>
<P>
   Top center story:
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-BORDER (Planeje, Yugoslavia) _ This village of 29
families _ nearly all the men are bakers _ was more or less leveled
in near-daily attacks by NATO planes in the weeks before the peace
agreement was signed. This is where some of the most furious
fighting of the war took place. At the time, refugees crossing the
border into Albania could actually hear the NATO bombs whistle down
before exploding. Now some villagers are returning to see the
damage NATO has done, and nearly everyone thinks NATO has an
obligation to help them rebuild. By Ian Fisher. (Moved in ``i''
news file.) 1,000 words.
</P>
<P>
   The story runs under a 3-column photo.
</P>
<P>
   Off-lead story:
</P>
<P>
   AMA-UNIONS (Undated) _ The American Medical Association votes to
form a union for doctors in what it calls an effort to level the
playing field with powerful managed care organizations. By Steven
Greenhouse. (Scheduled to move by 8 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   FOLD
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-MARINES _ U.S. Marines manning a checkpoint in Kosovo are
shot at by unknown persons and return fire, killing two people. By
Steven Lee Myers. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news
file.)
</P>
<P>
   reefer: GUNS-LAWSUITS (Undated) _ In the first sign of the
impact of the growing number of municipal lawsuits against the gun
industry, a well-known manufacturer of Saturday night specials in
suburban Los Angeles has filed for bankruptcy protection, raising
concern among city officials that other firearms companies may also
use bankruptcy to try to avoid the suits. By Fox Butterfield.
(Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
