<P>
   FOR THURSDAY AMs
</P>
<P>
   Business Day Front Page (coded ``f'')
</P>
<P>
   (Lede story)
</P>
<P>
   EUROPE-COKE (Brussels, Belgium) _ Belgian health authorities
ended a 10-day ban on Coca-Cola Co.'s products Wednesday,
permitting it to resume production in Belgium of sodas blamed for
249 cases of vomiting, cramps and other illnesses that shattered
European confidence in the world's best-known brand. By Alan
Cowell.
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Center display)
</P>
<P>
   BIOTECH-STORYTELLING (St. Louis) _ Jeremy Rifkin never misses a
chance to argue that the biotechnology industry is leading the
world toward environmental and social disaster. If he thinks it
will help slow the industry down, he is quick to file lawsuits and
promote boycotts or moratoriums. Last week, the activist happily
trekked to the headquarters of Monsanto Co. here to offer up his
vision of the future. By Barnaby J. Feder.
</P>
