<P>
   Corrects slugline on John Levesque's TV column for tomorrow,
from TV-CBS to TV-CBC, story being offered by the Seattle
Post-Intelligencer for clients of the NYTimes News Service for
editions of Thursday, June 24, and thereafter. If you have any
questions, please call Veronica Villarreal at (206) 448-8342.
</P>
<P>
   TV-CBC (Undated) _ With a French-Canadian surname like Levesque,
I'm genetically predisposed to watching CBC Television. This is
especially true in the summertime, when U.S. networks go on
vacation, figuring there aren't enough people watching TV to
warrant the introduction of fresh new programming.
</P>
<P>
   By John Levesque. (Story will move in the ``e'' category).
</P>
